# LiquidEther — Usage Guide

Interactive fluid-dynamics background for hero / landing sections.
Built with React + Three.js (WebGL). No extra CSS setup required.

---

## Installation

```bash
npm install three
```

Place `LiquidEther.jsx` and `LiquidEther.css` anywhere in your project
(e.g. `src/components/LiquidEther/`).

---

## Hero section pattern

The canvas fills its parent completely, so wrap it in a positioned container
and layer your content on top with `position: relative; z-index: 1`.

```jsx
import LiquidEther from './LiquidEther';

export default function Hero() {
  return (
    <section style={{ position: 'relative', width: '100%', height: '100vh' }}>
      {/* Fluid background — sits behind everything */}
      <LiquidEther
        colors={['#5227FF', '#FF9FFC', '#B19EEF']}
        mouseForce={20}
        cursorSize={100}
        isViscous
        viscous={30}
        iterationsViscous={32}
        iterationsPoisson={32}
        resolution={0.5}
        autoDemo
        autoSpeed={0.5}
        autoIntensity={2.2}
        takeoverDuration={0.25}
        autoResumeDelay={3000}
        autoRampDuration={0.6}
      />

      {/* Hero content — sits on top */}
      <div style={{ position: 'relative', zIndex: 1, padding: '4rem' }}>
        <h1>Your headline</h1>
        <p>Your subheading</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  );
}
```

---

## All props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `colors` | `string[]` | `['#5227FF','#FF9FFC','#B19EEF']` | Palette stops (1–N hex colors). Changing this rebuilds the WebGL context. |
| `mouseForce` | `number` | `20` | How strongly the cursor pushes the fluid. |
| `cursorSize` | `number` | `100` | Radius of the cursor influence area. |
| `isViscous` | `boolean` | `false` | Enable viscosity simulation (thicker fluid feel). |
| `viscous` | `number` | `30` | Viscosity coefficient (only used when `isViscous` is true). |
| `iterationsViscous` | `number` | `32` | Solver iterations for viscosity. Higher = more accurate, more GPU cost. |
| `iterationsPoisson` | `number` | `32` | Solver iterations for pressure. Higher = more accurate, more GPU cost. |
| `dt` | `number` | `0.014` | Simulation time-step. Lower = more stable, slower. |
| `BFECC` | `boolean` | `true` | Back-and-Forth Error Correction for advection. Smoother trails. |
| `resolution` | `number` | `0.5` | FBO resolution as a fraction of canvas size (0.25–1.0). |
| `isBounce` | `boolean` | `false` | Fluid bounces off canvas edges instead of wrapping. |
| `autoDemo` | `boolean` | `true` | Auto-animate when the cursor is idle or outside the canvas. |
| `autoSpeed` | `number` | `0.5` | Auto-demo cursor movement speed (normalized units/sec). |
| `autoIntensity` | `number` | `2.2` | Force multiplier applied during auto-demo. |
| `takeoverDuration` | `number` | `0.25` | Seconds to smoothly transition from auto to user control. |
| `autoResumeDelay` | `number` | `1000` | Milliseconds of idle time before auto-demo resumes. |
| `autoRampDuration` | `number` | `0.6` | Seconds to ramp up auto-demo speed after resuming. |
| `style` | `object` | `{}` | Inline styles forwarded to the container `<div>`. |
| `className` | `string` | `''` | Extra CSS class forwarded to the container `<div>`. |

---

## Notes

- The canvas is `position: absolute` inside the container — give the
  container a height (e.g. `height: 100vh`).
- Rendering pauses automatically when the component is scrolled out of
  view (IntersectionObserver) and when the browser tab is hidden
  (Page Visibility API).
- Only `colors` triggers a full WebGL rebuild. All other props update live
  without any flicker or restart.
- GPU resources (render targets, textures, renderer) are fully disposed
  when the component unmounts.
